menu "Storage"

    config STORAGE_NVS_NAMESPACE
        string "NVS namespace"
        default "wol"
        help
            The NVS namespace used to store all device credentials.
            Keep this short (max 15 chars). For an OPSEC-conscious
            deployment you may change this to a non-descriptive string
            (e.g. "d" or "cfg") so the namespace name gives no hint
            about the device's purpose to someone reading raw flash.

            Note: If you change this after devices have been provisioned
            the existing credentials become inaccessible (different
            namespace). Factory reset will be required.

endmenu
